entries.femaleVariant: Step back right this second!
Please step back.
Lookin' lost. Better turn right around.
'Ey!
Keep back.
Huh?
What the hell's that? Not allowed!
You hear me?!
[Pick up So Mi] I got her.
[Pick up So Mi] All right.
Place her here.
Take good care of her.
[Put down]
[Put down]
V, you risked your life to help me – to help our nation. That merits recognition.
You took an oath, V – purely symbolic, as patriotic rituals go. But that's why I'm doubly impressed.
Because you risked your life to help me – to help our nation.
[Take medal] Didn't expect this.
The medal is purely symbolic, of course.
Let me know when So Mi recovers?
When So Mi's better, you'll send word?
Not to worry – she'll recover.
So long, Rosalind.
We'll have our eye on you.
All right… I can't deny you tried to help her.
Thank you… for your service to the NUSA.
What about the help you promised me?
[Get out]
Right here, ma'am. Easy does it.
entries.maleVariant: Right here, sir. Easy does it.

entries.femaleVariant: Pull up here.
Step out of the vehicle, please.
Let’s go. Out of the car. Now.
Stand the fuck down! Can't you see she needs help?!
V, I need you to help her.
Don't worry, So Mi. We'll help, this'll be over soon.
Know you wanted her alive.
So what happens now?
Know you'd rather have had her alive.
It seems I have only myself to blame. I should have considered your abilities first. My apologies.
We say our goodbyes. You will return to your life, in Night City. I trust you'll find more success there than you did in Dogtown.
So long, Rosalind.
Best of luck, V. Perhaps one day you'll be called on to serve again.
Want nothin' more to do with you.
And… my reward? Remember being promised some help.
Don't contact me again. Ever. That clear?
In fact, we should charge you for the harm you've brought to the agency and the NUSA.
But the federal government isn't petty. As for compensation…
You were promised assistance for bringing So Mi in alive. If you failed to deliver your end of the bargain, why should we deliver ours?
I got it.
What happens now?
What'll happen to So Mi?
What'll happen to So Mi now?
FIA Special Agent Song So Mi was killed in the line of duty.
I'll make sure that's how she's remembered.
Mh, and how'll you remember her?
As my failure.
I could've done more for her, perhaps. Maybe all of us could have.
Got no regrets.
Sorry.
Did what I had to do. Don't regret a thing, conscience couldn't be clearer.
Look, sorry for how things turned out.
Don't be. You're another victim of this whole mess in a certain sense.
Don't feel like a victim.
Maybe you can tell me what that feels like someday.
Here's what I do know – you can only fool yourself for so long.
That would explain quite a lot, wouldn't it?
All politics to you, isn't it?
Liked you better when I was yankin' that tracker outta you.
Fake smile, hollow phrases, patronizing tone... See why you keep getting reelected.
Liked you better when I was rippin' that tracker outta your neck. You were just... you, then.
You'd be wise to remember who you're speaking to.
An' who would that be, exactly?
I'm still me, and the president.
Your compensation. We thank you for your service.
Contact who? This op never happened, remember?
So what happens now?
We say our goodbyes. You will return to Night City. Take pride in what you've achieved here, V.
You can help her... you're sure?
Rest easy, she'll be in excellent hands, receive the best care available on the continent.
She wanted to die, you know, over returning to the fold?
She's in pain, she's suffering. More than we can imagine.
But I've seen too much death – it's never the answer. I'm on the side of life.
Think she'll have a change of heart?
I know she will.
What now? What about the help I was promised?
Starting to have my doubts.
So Mi's alive, maybe she'll get better, but... this isn't what she wanted.
It's nothing to dwell on.
All I wanted to hear.
Maybe we should've listened to her.
Thanks. 'S all I wanted, needed to hear.
I know.
Easy for you to say.
Wrong, V. It's never easy.
Your actual compensation will be more practical. Reed will fill you in on the details.
'Kay, but you'll let me know, right? Let me talk to her?
I'm afraid that will be impossible.
National security demands that all that has transpired here will be classified top secret.
She asked me once if I… if I'd always be at her side when she fucked up. I said I wouldn't miss it for the world.
She didn't believe me, just smiled. She shook her head, she wasn't buyin' it, I could tell. Then, she dropped this bomb.
It's all yours, do what you will with it.
You're goin' home, So Mi. Be seein' you soon.
She asked me once if I… if I'd always be at her side when she fucked up. I said I wouldn't miss it for the world.
Know how it is to lose someone close.
So Mi... For all it's worth, I hope you're at peace.
She didn't believe me, just smiled. She shook her head, she wasn't buyin' it, I could tell. Then, she dropped this bomb.
Area secured. All clear for landing.
FIA special agent Terry. I'll have our people take the body.
No. V, could you carry So Mi...? Please.
Stretcher over here, stat!
[Shake hand] Madam President...
Good to see you, Madam President…
Rosalind, wait.
Rosalind, wait.
We're all set to go.
Good to see you, Madam President…
Bein' awful quiet. Everything all right?
Haven't said a word the whole way. What's eatin' you?
I think I'm all outta words for you.
Dunno... I dunno, V.
What happened down there – should talk about it.
Not my fault So Mi's dead.
Wanna talk about what happened?
Don't beat yourself up over this.
What happened back there… can tell it's eatin' at you. Wanna talk about it?
You wanna know what's eatin' at me? That I didn't get to her first. Ahead of you.
Reed...
Think it's my fault, don't you? Think I'm the reason she's dead?
I'd like to think you are.
Reed...
It's nobody's fault.
Not everything depends on you.
It's no one's fault, Reed.
Get a grip, Reed. Almost there.
Stop. Just stop.
So Mi chose this path. Nothin' was gonna change that.
Shame we'll never know if there's any truth to that.
Choice wasn't yours to make, Reed. Wasn't your fault.
Reed...?
Don't worry. I'm fine.
Don't worry. We'll finish this together.
Oh yeah, that's clear…
Wanna talk? Y'know, 'bout what happened?
Can't beat yourself to death over this, Reed.
I can't help stop seein' the same scene, like it's burned inside my dome.
What matters is she's alive, we're alive.
We're in a car, moving, leaving Brooklyn. She refuses to turn, look back.
No tears, no sobbing. Just a statement – "Seems like you saved my life." She doesn't believe it, I can hear she doesn't believe it.
Would she say the same now…?
Saved her then, saved her today.
Don't blame yourself.
Think you did. Think you saved her then, hope we'll save her again now.
Wish I could say, Reed. But don't blame yourself. No guarantee, none at all, that there's a way out for us.
We're in the same boat – clock's tickin' for both Song and me. Just hope the FIA's up to the task.
Of course.
Reed...?
Hey, don't worry. Plan to stick with you till the end, all right?
Reed…?
Riiight…
I wish I could say the same.
Likewise. Congratulations – I see the operation was a success.
I wonder now if she was right not to believe me. Or did I keep my promise after all?
"Lost all my friends when you recruited me," she says. "Now, don't you become my enemy, that's all I ask."
Listen, I need a few days to put together what we promised you. I trust that's no problem.
Medal and coin from Myers... they're tokens of important memories, never of regrets.
Time'll tell. Don't really know how I see 'em right now.
Yeah, gonna give it away, or sell it. Like So Mi.
Could end up as souvenirs. Or a warnin'. Only time'll tell.
Don't take this the wrong way, but I'll probably, uh, give it away, like So Mi did. Or sell it.
Gonna need serious scratch after you patch up my head.
"Lost all my friends when you recruited me," she says. "Now, don't you become my enemy, that's all I ask."
Was I a friend or an enemy... Fuck…
Give yourself time.
Know what it's like to lose someone close.
Can't beat yourself up over this. Reed. Need time, is all.
Y'know, Reed… got to know So Mi 'bout as well as you knew her. Ever wanna talk…
Mhm.
I should've looked her in the eye, heard her say she wanted out of life… I could've changed her mind.
Really think so?
It should've been me down there with So Mi, not you.
I think it's high time you headed back to Night City.
[Shake hand] Rosalind...
Rosalind.
V.
Hello, Rosalind.
V. Congratulations, you did fine work.
You all right?
You all right, Reed?
[Sit] You were a good friend to her.
[Sit] Can I help?
Think I might know how you feel.
Think I know how you're feelin', Reed… Know the pain.
Listen, there any way-- shit, sand's fuckin' hot…
entries.maleVariant: Listen, there any way-- shit, ground's fuckin' hot…

entries.femaleVariant: There any way I can help?
I need to help myself. I just don't know how.
All the questions you think of, then mull, with no prospect of ever getting an answer.
Mh. Questions without answers. About summed up my whole life there.
I've had time, V. Seven goddamn years.
[Sit] Maybe you had to become her enemy.
Maybe all of you… ah, shit, sand's fuckin' hot…
entries.maleVariant: Maybe all of you… shit, ground's fucking hot…

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah. At least one of us is sure of something.
Think you were all lookin' for something different, but… you weren't her enemy, Reed. Pretty darn sure of that.
Reed, I know that… shit, sand's fuckin' hot…
entries.maleVariant: Reed, I know that… shit, ground's fuckin' hot…

entries.femaleVariant: Maybe becoming her enemy was the sole way you could save her? Risked everything, both of you…
And we both have to pay the price?
Know you'd prolly rather not hear this now, but…
Reed, if Myers is lyin', if she doesn't save So Mi…
Means we gave Song somethin' worse than death…
You think I don't know that?
The FIA'll save her. She'll be all right.
Fine by me.
'Kay, then say nothin'. Not like I care.
Gotta get a grip.
Not everything depends on you, Reed.
Clearly.
Blamin' yourself for her death 'cause you think you had a say. 'Cept you didn't.
So Mi preferred death over going back to work for the FIA.
Song opted to die rather than fall into your hands. Know that, right?
Death is never the answer. I've seen too much of it already. Were I in her shoes, I would've chosen life.
Yeah, well, you weren't.
If I'm not mistaken, neither were you?
Mhm, how could I forget.
Fuck you. I'm done with your bullshit.
Fuck you, Myers, done with your bullshit. Let's wrap up this charade.
See why Reed didn't wanna work with you.
'Cause at day's end, it's just politics to you, isn't it?
Get why Reed didn't wanna work with you again.
Are you suggesting that your failure is my fault?
No. Just makin' sure you know you're a shitty boss.
You're sure you can help her?
She preferred to die than fall into your hands.
Both of you saved So Mi's life, V.
You can't put a price on that, but I'll try.
She'd better, Rosalind, she'd better.
Right – about that help you promised me…
What about the help you promised me?
Better not disappoint me.
Countin' on you, Myers. Don't disappoint.
Thank you, V, for your aid. I won't forget this.
[Sit] They were her mistakes, not yours.
They were-- shit, ground's hot…
They were her choices, Reed. Her mistakes, not yours.
I should've seen the consequences before it was too late.
Well, she did. Knew 'em and came to terms with 'em.
I failed her.
Yeah, you failed her. But that saved her.
Song didn't blame you for anything.
So Mi didn't blame you, and neither should you.
Long enough to start bein' honest with myself.
You failed her. Prolly not even the first time.
Thanks.
But that's also what saved her. She chose her own path. Not yours, not Myers'.
Always her way or the highway. Fuck. I just didn't think there'd be a four-hundred foot drop at the end of it.
So Mi's safe. Need to start lookin' out for yourself now.
Meanin' what, exactly?
You know what. Meanin' not gettin' sidelined, benched. Doubt you could take another seven years of that.
You're right, I couldn't.
You know So Mi got the same medal? Just after her first FIA op.
She gave it to a homeless man on Twenty-First. The guy just pinned it to his jacket like it was nothin' and asked for spare change.
[Sit]
Argh, sand's fuckin' hot…
That's the kind of person she was.
Make sure they help her.
You did everything you could.
'S just the kind of person Song was…
Unpredictable or uncompromising?
Walked her own paths only and always.
It's a shame we didn't know where they'd lead.
Sure, I'll wait.
Don't take too long.
Sure, I can wait. Few days won't kill me.
Rather you hurried up. Kinda livin' on borrowed time here.
Good.
I'm aware.
Dammit, V. Just damn.
Should never have recruited her.
It was a sign, Reed. Should never've recruited her, tried turning her into something she wasn't.
I didn't care if she was a patriot. I needed an agent.
There a difference?
Are there medias here? That why you're behaving like this?
Cool, so is this it? Gettin' down to brass tacks, droppin' the act, sendin' the paparazzi packin', wherever they are?
entries.maleVariant: Cool, so is this it? Gettin' down to brass tacks, droppin' the act, sendin' the paps packin', wherever they are?

entries.femaleVariant: Please step out of the vehicle.
Everything all right, ma'am?
Come on, V, she needs help.
Get it together, V.
Is there a problem?
It's yours now, ma'am.
Not to your liking?
V? The President would like a word.
Not about to shake your hand.
Won't shake your hand, Myers. Not after all this.
Surely, if there's any blame to lay here it would be at your feet, not mine.
Won't shake your hand, Myers. Not after all that happened.
As you wish. In any case, congratulations are in order. You did good work.
Rest assured no recordings of this meeting will appear anywhere. Officially, it's not taking place.
We did good, did the right thing. We'll get her help. But I can't…
We're losing time.
Ma'am, please, don't interfere.
At ease, V. No need to be formal. All's well that ends well.
You've nothing to say to me, is that it?
Should I take your silence to mean something?
Don't keep me waiting.
Is everything all right, V?
Is anything the matter?
My time is valuable, you seem to want to waste it…
V, where to? We really should talk.
No passage.
Keep moving.
Please do as instructed.
Turn back and follow all instructions.
Can’t loiter here.
Just gonna stand there?
Ma'am! Get back here immediately!
Proceed to the designated area immediately.
Stop right there.
V, what're you waiting for?
Do what they say, V. We don't have time.
Well? What is it?
You're wasting my time.
Here you are.
Ungh...
My time's worth millions, V.
Copy, I have eyes on 'em. Stand by to secure target.
Agh...
Ekh ekh...
Argh...
She's dead because of you.
You're the reason So Mi's dead – know that, right? That if you hadn't pushed her, past the Blackwall, off a goddamn cliff…?
I did not let that girl drag me around Dogtown by the nose simply to put her down. You know that, don't you?
That's right, you won't. And I'll never forget how So Mi begged me to end her life.
Poor girl.
Won't be missin' you, ever.
Good thing it'll be Reed. 'Cause I sure as shit can't stomach much more of you.
You should work on how you express gratitude, V. Good luck nonetheless.
I got 'er.
Rosalind, hope you'll understand one day.
Rosalind, truly hope one day you'll understand. Understand me, So Mi, Reed…
I'd wager I understand more than you think. Much more.
[Take medal] Am I supposed to be grateful?
Uh.. didn't expect this…
Mhm. This bauble a thinly-veiled attempt to buy my loyalty? My silence?
It's merely a token of my appreciation. I won't forget what you did for us, V.
So Mi told me she was beyond savin'.
Still got this itch, bothers me. So Mi said that it's too late, that she's beyond savin' already…
She's wrong. The best specialists work for us, world's top surgeons. We'll find a way.
Recovered the neural matrix – that's what counts.
Reed, Song's alive, neural matrix – we got it. That's what counts. A chance at life for her, and for me.
Yeah...
I don't need you hanging over me.
They'll serve as important reminders.
Heh, sure. If ever there're moments I chalk this up to some crazy dream, they'll serve as proof – that we really did go to hell and back.
So thanks, Reed.
I don't want a medal.
Didn't do all this for a medal, but because I had no choice. Tryin' to survive, not collect scrap.
I see... Very well, then. In spite of everything, I appreciate your help. It won't be forgotten.
Medal they tried to offer you... Know So Mi got the same exact one? Right after her first FIA op.
